I'm on the House floor tonight to fight against a bill that would claw back $9.4 billion in funding already approved by Congress—funding that supports public broadcasting, humanitarian aid and our national security.

@PBS and @NPR aren’t luxuries—they’re lifelines for rural communities like where I grew up in Buhl, Idaho and where I'm now proud to represent in Western Maryland. Cutting them hurts working families and future generations. We must do better.
https://t.co/GIzhieTobY
